{
  "doc_id": "18032",
  "text": "The efficacy of these specific exercises and the lumbar roll was evaluated by McKinney et al and indeed this was found to beneficial, [CITATION_1] but those data are limited and more studies are needed. Certainly, the head forward posture has been shown to be corrected by neck retractions. [CITATION_2] Lumbar rolls have been tested and found effective for low back pain, [CITATION_3] and again were a part of the therapy studied by McKinney et al. [CITATION_4] It may be more relevant that the patient comes to understand that any exercise, even when initially painful, is beneficial. Exercise therapy may actually have a profound psychological effect and only a limited physical effect. Nevertheless, if exercises are to be carried out, using the above exercises that have been shown to maintain or improve posture seems most appropriate.",
